==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Series winding
<hw>Series winding</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A winding in which the
armature coil and the field-magnet coil are in series with the external
circuits; -- opposed to <contr>shunt winding</contr>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Se"ries-wound`</wf>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

